  "title": "Admin Executive",
  "description": "<h3>About the Company</h3><p>Sentron Engineering provides electrical and mechanical engineering solutions. We work across different industries, offering services such as electrical design, mechanical engineering, energy management, and maintenance. Our experienced engineers focus on delivering quality work, understanding client needs, and providing energy-efficient solutions that meet local and international standards.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Prepare administrative documents such as reports, quotations, purchase orders, and contracts</p></li><li><p>Coordinate meetings and appointments with clients and internal teams</p></li><li><p>Maintain organized and accurate filing systems</p></li><li><p>Handle reception duties, including calls, visitors, and enquiries</p></li><li><p>Prepare and submit daily operational reports</p></li><li><p>Respond promptly to emails and faxes</p></li><li><p>Assist with contract documentation and deadline tracking</p></li><li><p>Perform other administrative tasks as required by management</p></li></ul><h3>Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>Good verbal and written communication skills</p></li><li><p>Strong organizational and multitasking abilities</p></li><li><p>Proficient in Microsoft Word, Excel, PowerPoint, and Outlook</p></li><li><p>Able to work well in a fast-paced environment</p></li><li><p>Detail-oriented with accurate documentation skills</p></li><li><p>Friendly, professional, and service-focused</p></li><li><p>Experience with quotations, procurement, and contract management is preferred</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of ACMV scope of work and equipment is required</p></li><li><p>Experience in the ACMV industry is an advantage</p></li></ul>",
